\": \"Regaining his top form, Paalam accomplished his mission of making the final two as he won all of his five bouts.\", \"from\": 1175, \"to\": 1287, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He started his campaign with a pair of unanimous decision victories overGreece's Alexei LagkazasviliandTurkmenistan's Shukur Ovezovbefore he edgedArmenia's Artur Bazeyanin the last 16, winning via a tiebreak.\", \"from\": 1289, \"to\": 1497, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The pride of Bukidnon then toppledDominican Republic's Jose Luis delos Santos Felizvia unanimous decision in the quarterfinals to set up a clash with Siwach.\", \"from\": 1499, \"to\": 1656, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1512, \"end\": 1520, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bukidnon\", \"score\": 0.9999993635323996, \"rank\": 6.364679110647401e-07, \"text\": \"Bukidnon\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bukidnon\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bukidnon\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"With three Paris seats up for grabs in his division, Paalam could have still remained in contention even if he fell to the Indian as the losers in the semifinals lock horns in a box off for the last Olympic slot.\", \"from\": 1658, \"to\": 1870, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1669, \"end\": 1674, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999885981198, \"rank\": 1.1401874013153e-08, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 1781, \"end\": 1787, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Indian_people\", \"score\": 0.8770522671795299, \"rank\": 0.14015358014742416, \"text\": \"Indian\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Indian_people\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Indian_people\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But Paalam refused to take the risk and left it all in the ring against the taller Siwach, who failed to t